# Data directory for AI Engine

## Structure:

```
data/
├── raw/
│   ├── stressed/       # Audio files with stress/distress
│   └── non_stressed/   # Normal/calm audio files
├── processed/          # Preprocessed audio
└── augmented/          # Augmented training data
```

## Audio Format:
- Format: WAV (preferred) or MP3
- Sample Rate: 22050 Hz (will be resampled if different)
- Duration: Any (will be processed appropriately)
- Channels: Mono (stereo will be converted)

## Data Sources:
You can use existing datasets like:
- RAVDESS (Ryerson Audio-Visual Database of Emotional Speech)
- TESS (Toronto Emotional Speech Set)
- CREMA-D (Crowd-sourced Emotional Multimodal Actors Dataset)
- Your own recorded samples

## Labeling:
- Stressed: distress calls, screams, panicked speech, crying
- Non-stressed: normal conversation, calm speech

Place audio files in respective directories before training.